The described three parts of the curve τc(Axy) have sigmoid profiles, which is the result of the competition between shear band dilatancy and poroelastic contraction of blocks due to fluid outflow. Analysis of the obtained result allowed to formulate the following general dependence of the shear strength of constrained shear band zones on the parameter Axy. The dependence is expressed as a sum of a constant and three sigmoid contributions (curve 1 in Fig. 6a):5\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
